cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CC, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL) as it deals with metaphor paraphrase aptness judgments. The use of a composite DNN also suggests that it could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study of context and its effect on the judgments could also place it under computational linguistics (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of crowd-sourcing for the first experiment could suggest that it could also fall under computer-human interaction (cs.CC).
